Java Swing Circle Drawing Application
Description

This project is a Java Swing GUI application that demonstrates event handling and custom drawing.
The application displays a window containing two buttons—Draw Circle and Clear—along with a drawing panel.

When the user clicks Draw Circle, a filled circle is drawn at a random position inside the panel.
When Clear is clicked, all drawings are removed and the panel becomes blank again.

Features

Java Swing based graphical user interface

Button click handling using ActionListener

Custom drawing using paintComponent()

Random positioning of shapes

Clear and redraw functionality

Technologies Used

Java

Java Swing

AWT Graphics

Event Handling (ActionListener)

How the Program Works

The application window is created using JFrame.

Two buttons are added: Draw Circle and Clear.

A custom panel overrides paintComponent() to draw graphics.

Clicking Draw Circle generates a random position and draws a filled circle.

Clicking Clear removes all drawings and refreshes the panel.

How to Run

Open the project in any Java IDE (Eclipse, IntelliJ, NetBeans).

Compile and run the file containing the main() method.

Click Draw Circle to draw a circle.

Click Clear to remove all drawings.

Output

A window with two buttons and a drawing area

Randomly positioned filled circles

Instant panel update on button click

